trips.name: Drift Boat With Beau
trips.notes: Caught tons of little rainbows, and a few decent sized ones. Hitting mostly smaller nymphs - pheasant tails and prince nymphs.

trips.name: Old Post 2017
trips.notes: Awesome few days, 5 pike over 40", tons of high 30s. Biggest walleye around 23".

trips.name: Kingston 2017
trips.notes: Good couple days. Not a ton of action for big fish, but a lot of smaller fish action.

trips.name: Christmas Eve 2016
trips.notes: 2x Cohen, 2x Tim. Tim caught possibly the biggest Pike in Wildwood.

trips.name: Port Albert, Fall 2016
trips.notes: Caught one night fishing at the baskets. Still fished a lot in front of Demetre's, but caught nothing.

trips.name: Belwood Lake & Dam
trips.notes: Eli caught an okay bass at the dam. Nothing in the big lake. The lake was drained 30+ feet.

trips.name: Cocoa Charter
trips.notes: Nothing big, but several different species and a lot of fun! Went with Fineline Fishing Charters.

trips.name: Guelph
trips.notes: Caught squat. Not even a hit. Canoed on the south part of Guelph Lake (flood plane). Depth was 2-4' around the edges and 5-7' near the broken trees.

trips.name: Balls Bridge
trips.notes: I got two suckers, everyone else got some small to medium sized smallies.

trips.name: Wildwood With Parents
trips.notes: Biggest fish was Dad's 28.5" Pike.  All fish were caught really close to shore, within 10 feet. Tubes seemed to be the bait of choice.

trips.name: Grand River Trout
trips.notes: Eli caught two 8.5-9" browns. I caught dick all.

trips.name: Bass Lake With Denny
trips.notes: Perch, crappie, walleye, pike; all pretty small.

trips.name: Port Albert
trips.notes: Incredible couple of days. Over 29 fish in two days.

entries.name: Trout - Rainbow
entries.notes: Virtually still water. First decent catch on The Bow with a fly!

entries.name: Trout - Rainbow
entries.notes: Caught in the fast water in the fork opening.

entries.name: Steelhead
entries.notes: Caught casting upstream, right against the bank in medium moving water.

entries.name: Steelhead
entries.notes: Casting downstream close to shore in very slow water.

entries.name: November 12, 2016
entries.notes: Medium size female. Got away before I could get a photo.

entries.name: Trout - Speckled Sea
entries.notes: Biggest was a couple pounds, others were very small. Katee caught one.

entries.name: Ladyfish
entries.notes: Quick retrieve, no jigging. Caught by Katee.

entries.name: Bass - Smallmouth
entries.notes: Caught 4 decent sized smallies throughout the day. Not all picture worthy.

entries.name: aaaa7692-e73c-4fb1-8488-ffb986a12ca4
entries.notes: Caught 2 throughout the day, the biggest was 13.5 inches.

entries.name: 75082cd1-f11a-4bfa-a5ff-c27dc8da512b
entries.notes: Bait set 1-2 feet below the ice.

entries.name: 552d79b5-4897-48b5-9eaa-762fa0b608a0
entries.notes: Four pike ranging from 17"-21" and 1-2 lbs. between 1:46pm and 4:18pm.

entries.name: 8d67ae59-9fde-4fd9-80ce-576dc40bec90
entries.notes: Caught a bunch of tiny bass. Just a good day on the river with the bros.
